              "content": "<p> <strong>Jubilee Songs</strong> are Protestant hymns of celebration, joy, and renewal. “Give Me That Old-Time Religion” dates from at least 1289/1873, when it was first included in a list of Jubilee Songs, although the roots of the hymn are likely much older, even possibly going back to African-American Spirituals in their confluence with White Gospel music, forming what is called Southern Gospel songs. “Give Me That Old-Time Religion” is a standard in many Protestant hymnals, although, interestingly, it does not mention Jesus Christ or the Gospels. There are different lyrics for the hymn, but some of the most common run as follows:</p><p>Give me that Old-Time Religion.         It was good for my old mother.              It was good for the Hebrew Children.<br />Give me that Old-Time Religion.         It was good for my old mother.              It was good for the Hebrew Children.<br />Give me that Old-Time Religion:         It was good for my old mother.              It was good for the Hebrew Children.<br />It’s good enough for me.                       And it’s good enough for me.                And it’s good enough for me.</p><p>It was good for the Prophet Moses.      It was good for the Prophet David.         It was good for Prophet Daniel.</p><p>It was good for the Prophet Moses.      It was good for the Prophet David.         It was good for Prophet Daniel.</p><p>It was good for the Prophet Moses.      It was good for the Prophet David.         It was good for Prophet Daniel.</p><p>And it’s good enough for me.               And it’s good enough for me.                 And it’s good enough for me.</p><p>It was good for Paul and Silas.            Well, give me that Old-Time Religion.   Say: Give me that Old-Time Religio<br />It was good for Paul and Silas.            Well, give me that Old-Time Religion.   Well, that Old-Time Religion.<br />It was good for Paul and Silas:            Give me that Old-Time Religion:            I want that Old-Time Religion:<br />And it’s good enough for me.              It’s good enough for me.                         It’s good enough for me.</p><p>                                                             It was good for my old father.<br />                                                             It was good for my old father.<br />                                                             It was good for my old father:<br />                                                             And it’s good enough for me. </p>",
              "sectionId": "book-purpose-profile"
